---
import LegalLayout from '@templates/LegalLayout.astro';
import { SITE, LEGAL, CONTACT, PENDIENTE } from '@lib/site';

const lang = 'en' as const;
---

<LegalLayout
  lang={lang}
  pageKey="privacy"
  title="Privacy policy | Alma Mía"
  description="Privacy policy of Alma Mía pursuant to the GDPR and the Spanish Data Protection Act (LOPDGDD): what data we process, for what purpose, legal basis, retention and the rights of users."
  h1="Privacy policy"
  lastUpdated="14/06/2026"
>
  <p>
    This privacy policy describes how {SITE.brand} processes the personal data that users
    provide through {SITE.domain}, in accordance with Regulation (EU) 2016/679 (GDPR) and the
    Spanish Organic Law 3/2018 on the Protection of Personal Data and the guarantee of digital
    rights (LOPDGDD).
  </p>

  <h2>1. Data controller</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Controller:</strong> {LEGAL.titularName} {LEGAL.titularName === PENDIENTE && '(pending completion)'}</li>
    <li><strong>NIF/NIE:</strong> {LEGAL.nif}</li>
    <li><strong>Address:</strong> {LEGAL.address}</li>
    <li><strong>Email:</strong> {CONTACT.email}</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. Data we process and purpose</h2>
  <p>
    Through the contact form we process the data you provide (name, email, telephone, area,
    date, number of guests and the message) for the purpose of handling your request for
    information and, where applicable, preparing a service proposal.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Legal basis</h2>
  <p>
    The legal basis for the processing is your consent, which you give when submitting the form,
    and the application of pre-contractual measures at your request. You may withdraw your
    consent at any time.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Data retention</h2>
  <p>
    We will retain your data for as long as necessary to handle your request and, if no
    contractual relationship is formalised, for the period legally required to address possible
    liabilities.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Recipients</h2>
  <p>
    Your data will not be disclosed to third parties except where legally required. To send the
    form emails we use an email delivery service provider (data processor) that acts in
    accordance with our instructions and with the appropriate safeguards.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Users' rights</h2>
  <p>
    You may exercise your rights of access, rectification, erasure, objection, restriction of
    processing and data portability by writing to {CONTACT.email}. You also have the right to
    lodge a complaint with the Spanish Data Protection Agency
    (<a href="https://www.aepd.es" rel="noopener" target="_blank">www.aepd.es</a>) if you
    consider that the processing does not comply with the regulations.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Security measures</h2>
  <p>
    {SITE.brand} applies the appropriate technical and organisational measures to ensure the
    security of personal data and to prevent its alteration, loss or unauthorised access.
  </p>

  <p>
    <em>The data marked as {PENDIENTE} must be completed with the controller's actual tax
    information before the site is published.</em>
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
